<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
      .a{
        color: aqua;
      }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1 class="a" id="a">Hello</h1>
  <h1 class="a" id="b">hola</h1>
  <h1 class="b" id="c">Namaste</h1>
    <script>
        // let js = document.getElementById('a');
        // console.log(js);
        // let q = document.getElementsByClassName('a');
        // console.log(q);

        let k = document.createElement('h1');
        k.className = 'b';
        k.textContent = 'Hello';
        console.log(k)
        document.body.appendChild(k);

        const t=['Akshith',"ashish",'Jaydeep']
        for(let i=1;i<t.length;i++){
            let tt=document.createElement('h1')
            tt.className='aa'
            tt.textContent=t[i];
            console.log(tt)
            //console.log(t[i]),console.log(t)
        }

        let title
        for(let i=0;i<3;i++){
            title=document.createElement();
            title.classMame='t'
            // title.style.fontsize='24px'
            title.textContent=i
            console.log(title)
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>

Notes:
getElementbyClassName:
returns all the elements having the same class name.
getElementbyClassName():
method returns an HTML collection object
an html collection is array like 
length property provides the size of the collection.

QuerySelector:
used to select HTML element by its classname,tagname; it selects only first element.

QuerySelectorAll:
can be used to select HTML 

manipulate elements:
To create a HTML element;
--create element()
--document.createElement()
--the method takes an HTML element tag name as String parameter

Manipulate Elements:
To create a HTML element
•	createElement()
•	the method used to create a html element
•	let k = document.createElement('h1');
•	        k.className = 'b';
•	        k.textContent = 'Hello';
•	        console.log(k)
•	        document.body.appendChild(k);

In DOM all elements are defined as objects
	Property: is a value that you can set to the objects.(like changing the content of html element)
	Method: an action (like add or delete)
	Getting element by id
	let js = document.getElementById('a');
	        console.log(js);


	Getting element by classname
	Returns all the elements having the same class name.
	let q = document.getElementsByClassName('a');
        console.log(q);
	        for(let i=0;i<q.length;i++){
	          console.log(q[i]);
	        }
	

	Getting element by tagname
	let k = document.getElementsByTagName('h1');
        document.write(k);

	Getting element by query selector

	Used to select HTML element with classname, tagname 
